item.title: MacKenzie Scott files for divorce from second husband
item.description: Billionaire philanthropist MacKenzie Scott has filed for divorce from her second husband after less than two years of marriage.

item.title: Floating cars, submerged buildings and no power: Florida residents describe what Hurricane Ian looks like
item.description: in Naples, Florida, on Wednesday afternoon, Lauren Barlow watched as water crept in through her home's door and began rising across the first floor.

item.title: Donald Trump actually doesn't like firing people in person
item.description: Donald Trump's place in the public consciousness -- prior to 2016, that is -- revolved around two words: "You're fired."

item.title: What to make of the latest reports from Russia
item.description: Get out of Russia is the US Embassy's warning to Americans.

item.title: Hurricane Ian makes landfall in southwest Florida as Category 4 storm with 150-mph winds
item.description: Hurricane Ian makes landfall in southwest Florida on Wednesday and is bringing a catastrophic trifecta of high winds, heavy rain and historic storm surge to the state.

item.title: Hurricane Ian makes landfall in Florida
item.description: Hurricane Ian, a powerful Category 4 storm, has made landfall in Southwest Florida. Follow here for the latest.

item.title: Katie Couric reveals she was diagnosed with breast cancer
item.description: Veteran journalist Katie Couric reported some personal news on Wednesday.

item.title: Dogs can smell when humans are stressed, study suggests
item.description: Dogs were able to differentiate the smells from breath and sweat samples taken from people before and after they were stressed, according to a new study.

item.title: Hurricane hunter: Flight to Hurricane Ian 'worst I've ever been on'
item.description: Aerospace engineer Nick Underwood, who flew into Hurricane Ian in the early morning hours Wednesday, said the flight was the worst of his career.

item.title: Volkswagen to price Porsche IPO at the high end
item.description: Volkswagen said Wednesday that it is pricing the Porsche initial public offering at €82.50 a share, which will raise approximately €9.4 billion.

item.title: First on CNN: Unvaccinated individuals 14 times more likely to get monkeypox than vaccinated, new US data shows
item.description: Eligible individuals who did not receive the monkeypox vaccine were around 14 times likelier to become infected with the virus than those who were vaccinated, according to federal government data posted by the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

item.title: Lizzo played James Madison's 200-year-old crystal flute at her Washington, DC concert
item.description: The "About Damn Time" singer and accomplished flutist carefully played the delicate woodwind, which was sent as a gift to James Madison in 1813 by a French flute maker. The Library of Congress allowed Lizzo to play the flute onstage.

item.title: Hilaree Nelson's body found after US ski mountaineer dies during Nepal expedition
item.description: The body of Hilaree Nelson was found Wednesday and taken to a forensic laboratory in Kathmandu for an autopsy after the renowned US ski mountaineer died during an expedition in Nepal, according to Sachindra Kumar Yadav, an official with the tourism department.

item.title: One person dead, another in custody following shooting at Arkansas hospital, police say
item.description: One person was killed in a shooting at a hospital in the suburbs of Little Rock, Arkansas, on Wednesday, according to the Sherwood Police Department.

item.title: Former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo to start political action committee and launch podcast
item.description: Former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo on Wednesday announced plans to create a new political action committee dedicated to helping "elect the right people to office." He also revealed plans to form an organization focused on gun violence issues.

item.title: Danielle Pinnock went from spoofing Hollywood to starring in one of its hottest comedies
item.description: Danielle Pinnock can thank her mother's wig for helping her get the role of a lifetime.

item.title: September 28, 2022 Russia's war in Ukraine-Ukraine news
item.description: Unexplained leaks have been found in two Russian undersea gas pipelines to Europe. Experts say the possibility of sabotage on the Nord Stream pipelines cannot be ruled out. Follow here for live updates.

item.title: Joe Biden's latest gaffe plays right into Republicans' hands
item.description: President Joe Biden once called himself a "gaffe machine" -- and his latest slip-up is a whopper.

item.title: Biden asks if deceased congresswoman is present at White House food insecurity conference
item.description: President Joe Biden on Wednesday asked if a congresswoman who died last month was present at a White House food insecurity conference.

item.title: 'Cobra Kai' hasn't lost its kick as it keeps 'Karate Kid'-ing around
item.description: Crossing the streams with its sequels, the fifth season of "Cobra Kai" features heavy dollops of the second and third "The Karate Kid" movies while continuing to carve out its own next-generation melodrama, all in extraordinarily nimble fashion. While it's not the best series on TV (OK, Netflix), there should be some kind of prize for the best revival culled from limited source material.

item.title: FDA proposes updates to 'healthy' claim on food packages
item.description: The US Food and Drug Administration is proposing changes to the nutrition standards that foods must meet before they can carry the "healthy" label on their packages.

item.title: 'No matter the law, no matter the stigma, no matter the cost.' This European network helps people access abortions
item.description: Meet the B&B owners, the doctors and activists who form part of a grassroots web, working around the clock to assist those who need to travel to the Netherlands for a second-trimester termination.

item.title: Alzheimer's drug slows progression of cognitive decline in clinical trial, drugmakers say
item.description: A monoclonal antibody treatment for Alzheimer's disease called lecanemab slows the progression of cognitive decline by 27% compared with a placebo, drugmakers Biogen and Eisai said Tuesday.

item.title: US scrambles F-15 jet to shoot down Iranian drone that appeared to threaten US forces in Iraq
item.description: The US scrambled an F-15 jet to shoot down an Iranian drone that appeared to be heading towards US forces in Erbil, Iraq, on Wednesday, a US official told CNN.

item.title: Airports and airlines brace for a major impact from Hurricane Ian
item.description: Airlines, airports and the federal government are bracing for aviation infrastructure to take a major blow from Hurricane Ian. Cancellations and closures are already piling up across the Florida.

item.title: Stocks, bonds rally after Bank of England says it will buy UK debt
item.description: US stocks and bonds rallied Wednesday after the Bank of England said it would buy UK government debt "on whatever scale is necessary" in an emergency intervention to halt a bond market crash.

item.title: LAPD identifies suspect in fatal shooting of rapper PnB Rock and arrests 2 others
item.description: Freddie Lee Trone is considered armed and dangerous, police said.

item.title: Lucas Papademos Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Fast Facts about Lucas Papademos and learn more about the economist and former prime minister of Greece.

item.title: Hurricane Ian could push food prices even higher
item.description: Hurricane Ian is the latest natural disaster to impact food prices. The storm hitting Florida is already forcing orange juice futures to rise, and it may soon squeeze the country's fertilizer supply — which could have a far-reaching impact.

item.title: The ways Hurricane Ian is an unprecedented storm for Florida's Gulf Coast
item.description: If Hurricane Ian makes landfall with maximum winds of at least 155 mph, it will be the most intense storm on record for the west coast of the Florida Peninsula.
